The paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of neural machine translation in low-resource settings, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and model adaptation, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image captioning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of BLEU scores as a metric for evaluating translation quality, which is a common practice in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
